1. Can you please specify what are programming languages which are compiled to another programming languages?

A: ClojureScript (https://clojurescript.org) is one such language (a slight variant of Clojure) and it comes with a compiler that compiles its programs into Java Script. It looks like there are not many tools that do such translations. Such compilers are also referred to as source-to-source compilers or trans compilers.


